	   <h2 class = "concept-title"> Use Classes: Send Text </h2>
	   <div class = "concept-description">
	<p> To send a text message using code, Twilio allows software developers to programmatically make and receive phone calls and send and receive text messages using its web service APIs. Twilio does not come with the Python standard library. Twilio is one of the thousands of external Python packages that are available to download and use. Here is a video that shows you how to manually install the Python package Twilio on your system : <a href = "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OfvdONdp5GI&feature=youtu.be">Twilio Install</a> and link for <a href = "https://www.twilio.com/docs/python/install">Download</a> After download, sign up <a href = "https://www.twilio.com/try-twilio"> here </a></p>
	<p><b>1. from twilio import rest</b><br><br>
# Your Account Sid and Auth Token from twilio.com/user/account<br>
<b>2. account_sid = "AC32a3c49700934481addd5ce1659f04d2"&nbsp; # account_sid and auth_token , you will find in your account after you <br>
3. auth_token = "{{ auth_token }}"&nbsp; # signed up <br>
4. client = rest.TwilioRestClient(account_sid, auth_token)<br><br>
5. message = client.messages.create (<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;   body= " I love Udacity ",<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; to= " +14159352345 ",&nbsp; # Replace with your phone number which you registered with twilio <br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; from_= " +14158141829 ")&nbsp; # Replace with your Twilio number which you received from twilio while sign up <br>
6. print message.sid</b><br>
<p> In first line, we use Python keyword from. Keywords in Python are reservered words that cannot be used as ordinary
identifiers. from keyword explained that for importing a specific variable, class or a function from a module. So, from twilio.rest import TwilioRestClient --> telling computer is that inside Twilio, there is a folder called rest and inside that folder is a class called twiliorestclient and use that class inside our code.</p>
<p> Now, we know that when we downloaded Twilio, we got, among other things, a folder called twilio. And inside that foler is a folder called rest. Inside rest, is a python file, which has a class called TwilioRestClient. When we say rest.TwilioRestClient(), we are calling the __init __function defined inside the class. And that creates an instance or object. We call that instance client, and then we can do stuff with that instance, like send SMSes.   
